                   "message":  "GITIGNORE-VERIFY-TARGET-DIR: gitignore the verify-gate\u0027s target-local-verify build dir\n\nThe canonical verify gate\u0027s environment produces a target-local-verify/ cargo\ntarget directory inside the dispatch worktree. The existing /target/ + **/target/\nrules don\u0027t match it (different dir name), so git add -A swept ~1205\ntarget-local-verify/** build-artifact files into a commit during #275 (caught and\nreset before push). Added /target-local-verify/ + **/target-local-verify/ under\nthe Build outputs section so it is always ignored.\n\ngit grep confirms no committed file references target-local-verify (it is local\ngate tooling output, not a script to edit), and no currently-tracked file is\naffected. .gitignore is the only change.\n\nVerified: git check-ignore matches the new rule (root + nested); a real\ntarget-local-verify/ dir no longer shows as untracked; canonical gate VERIFY OK.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
